Analysis  Reflection I did not enjoy this poem at all. It was way too long for my tastes, and I felt like there wasn't too much content that struck me (essentially, a lot of filler content). However, the end of the poem was a hard hitting one for me.
 &ldquo;yellow crowfoot in the pond, not lotus, not lily&rdquo;
 This was hard hitting for me as it made me remember to be grateful for what I have, and to not take anything for granted again.
